In this presidential memorandum issued by Donald J. Trump on March 27, 2017, he establishes the White House Office of American Innovation (OAI) to ensure that America remains a global innovation leader. The OAI will bring together ideas from the government, private sector, and thought leaders to solve problems and create opportunities. The memorandum outlines the establishment, mission, and responsibilities of the OAI, which include making recommendations to the President on improving government operations, services, and quality of life for Americans, as well as spurring job creation. The OAI will gather information and ideas from various sources and produce reports with policy recommendations for the President.